did.unittitle: International Brotherhood of Teamsters Benefits Department Records
did.abstract: This collection consists of Summary Plan Descriptions (SPDs) which are printed booklets distributed to local or group members to explain the benefits covered under local or multi-employer contracts.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is arranged by individual Summary Plan Description.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: This collection was transferred to the Teamsters Labor HIsotry Research Center from the IBT.

did.abstract: This collection consists of summary plan descriptions (SPDs) for regional and/or local union organizations of the IBT. SPDs generally spell out the condiditons of coverage and the details of various benefits - life insurance, accidental death and dismemberment, weekly accident and sickness, etc. The SPDs collected here were negotated at the local or regional level. These rfepresent record copies maintained by the IBT Benefits Department.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: These SPD's spell out the details of benefits coverage for local and/or reginal IBT union organizations.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Collection: IBT Benefits Department records Organized into one series: Summary Plan Descriptions The SPDs are arranged individually and labeled as to local or regional union organization.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.
